FaceTime HD Camera Fix on Fedora running on MacBook Pro 2015
=============================================================

This repository is a self-contained distribution of the FaceTime HD
camera Linux driver, with patches that fix the frozen-frame bug on
kernel 6.15+.

It contains code from the following upstream projects:

1. patjak/facetimehd  (the V4L2 kernel driver)
   https://github.com/patjak/facetimehd
   License: GPL-2.0-only
   Authors: Patrik Jakobsson, Sven Schnelle, and contributors
   Location in this repo: driver/

2. patjak/facetimehd-firmware  (the firmware extraction tooling)
   https://github.com/patjak/facetimehd-firmware
   License: GPL-2.0
   Authors: Patrik Jakobsson and contributors
   Location in this repo: firmware-extractor/

The vendored copies preserve all upstream copyright notices and
license headers. Files modified by this repository are marked at
the top of the file with a "Modified ... by vitaliebumbu" notice
listing the changes, in compliance with GPL-2.0 §2(a).

This repository does NOT contain Apple's proprietary firmware blob.
The firmware-extractor downloads it directly from Apple's update
servers at install time, the same way the upstream tooling does.

For a list of changes made in this repository, see CHANGES.md.
